thods and documentation. The ISSO implements security controls and manages authentication and intrusion detection software and devices. You will oversee the activities of the program\u2019s IT Specialists. The execution of all duties and responsibilities for this position requires the candidate to be physically present in Burlington, VT. Implement and maintain the security requirements as defined by the client. (40%) Inventory management and document maintenance (40%) Risk Analysis and Management (10%) Change management (10%) Required Technical and Professional Expertise Linux/UNIX experience (3 years) Strong Organizational skills Office Administration MS Office Proficiency Security and Information Assurance skills Security Clearance: Current DoD Government Security Clearance (active within last 2 years) Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise Security and Information Assurance skills Linux systems knowledge Semiconductor Manufacturing Experience / Theory DoD 8570 Compliant Security Certification such as Security+, CISSP or CISM About Business Unit IBM Services is a team of business, strategy and technology consultants that design, build, and run foundational systems and services that is the backbone of the world's economy. IBM Services partners with the world's leading companies in over 170 countries to build smarter businesses by reimagining and reinventing through technology, with its outcome-focused methodologies, industry-leading portfolio and world class research and operations expertise leading to results-driven innovation and enduring excellence. Your Life @ IBM What matters to you when you\u2019re looking for your next career challenge? Maybe you want to get involved in work that really changes the world? What about somewhere with incredible and diverse career and development opportunities \u2013 where you can truly discover your passion? Are you looking for a culture of openness, collaboration and trust \u2013 where everyone has a voice? What about 